feat(R64): APTD warpres 5000-step long run -- turnaround, Pareto-dominates the Bridge

Two trajectories (warpres, 5000 steps, A40; flow_scale 0.15 ~ 0.3 identical), 1-NFE:
  step 1000  SSIM 0.215 PSNR 12.3 LPIPS 0.424
  step 2000  SSIM 0.255 PSNR 13.6 LPIPS 0.443
  step 3000  SSIM 0.285 PSNR 14.1 LPIPS 0.517
  step 5000  SSIM 0.302 PSNR 14.3 LPIPS 0.665
Bridge ref (s2_base best-val, velocity/4NFE): SSIM 0.249 / PSNR 13.55 / LPIPS 0.509.

A single APTD model traverses the perceptual-distortion frontier; the Bridge operating
point is Pareto-DOMINATED. best-SSIM 0.302 vs 0.249 (+21%, robust); best-LPIPS 0.424 vs
0.509 (-17%); a balanced point (~step 2000, 1-NFE) beats Bridge on ALL THREE simultaneously
(SSIM 0.255 / PSNR 13.59 / LPIPS 0.443) at 1/4 the NFE. R63 ablation showed the warp+residual
decomposition is what enables this.

Honest: step-2000 SSIM/PSNR margins are small (n=54, need bootstrap), LPIPS win robust; late
training over-blurs (LPIPS degrades chasing MSE) so best-val should use a balanced/perceptual
criterion or a light perceptual term; flow_scale not a key lever; APTD x0/1NFE vs Bridge
velocity/4NFE (R63 internal ablation is the single-factor control).

Next: pick ~step-2000 operating point + bootstrap CIs for the final table; optional light
perceptual term to hold SSIM+LPIPS together; then add PMOS as the second module.
